description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for staff within Lancashire and South Cumbria NHS Foundation Trust to apply to be part of our 8th cohort of Apprentice Trainee Nursing Associates. This is part of a National programme and is working in partnership with local NHS partners and the University of Central Lancashire and University of Cumbria.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These posts are apprenticeship posts which will see you develop to a Nursing Associate on successful completion of your 2 year training programme. The course is fully funded and you will receive paid study to attend the University of Central Lancashire or University of Cumbria.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If successful in securing a place on the course you WILL NOT be eligible for student finance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Trainees will be based within clinical practice for the duration of the programme and will be supported throughout the course by the highly experienced course team working closely with UCLAN and the University of Cumbria. There is an expectation that you will rotate through different services within your speciality (where applicable) and undertake block placements outside of your normal place of work, which will be organised by the Practice Education Team (PEF) in Lancashire &amp; South Cumbria NHS FT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be some travel required so you must either be a car driver or be prepared to access public transport when on placement. You could be expected to travel up to 90 minutes each way to placement and work shifts and weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On completion of the course you will be placed into a permanent band 4 Nursing Associate role however, this may not be in your current work place.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;During training you will be paid a Band 3 and work on a rotational basis within a number of service areas both within our Trust and placement experience in partnership organisations to gain a breadth of experience and skills. &lt;br /&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic, motivated staff who want to assist us in improving care for patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holders will have good communication skills and be able to work as part of a team.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be required to work 37.5 hours.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In order to apply for the course you will need to have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maths and English (See acceptable qualifications below)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;48 UCAS Points&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12 months health care experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;The entry criteria for the course and are the following qualifications:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Maths &amp; English at:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;GCSE English and Maths (grade C or 4 and above)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Level 2 Functional skills Maths&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Level 2 Functional skills English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Key Skills Level 2 application of number or numeracy (Pass)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Key Skills Level 2 Communication (Pass)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CSE (Grade 1) Maths&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CSE (Grade 1) English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Level 2 certificates (Grade C or 4 and above)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Core maths level 3 (Grade E or above)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pre U Certificate (P3 or above)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Freestanding Mathematics - Foundations of Advanced Mathematics (Grade C)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you do not have maths and English or original certificates, you will either not be shortlisted and/or you will not be offered an interview. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;48 UCAS Points:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have 48 UCAS points such as:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A-Levels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diploma&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foundation degree / Degree&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Level 4 NVQ&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BTEC (Dependant on the level)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you do not have the above UCLAN will accept the following qualifications with 12 months health care experience:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NVQ Level 3 + 12 months care experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NVQ Level 2 + 12 months care experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Care Certificate + 12 months care experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOU MUST HAVE THE ORIGINAL CERTIFICATES.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have the Original certificates for Maths, English and any qualifications. Copies and transcripts will not be accepted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must also clearly put Maths, English and other qualifications, with your type/level of qualification, grade and date achieved, on you application form in order to be shortlisted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For internal candidates – you will need to have agreement from your manager to apply for this post, which will be verified if successful.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Further details with regards to the role can be found in the attached Job Description and Person Specification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;External &amp; Internal vacancies &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;These posts are open to both internal candidates (who may want to complete the programme in a different network or team) and open to external candidates and bank staff, who do not work in Lancashire &amp; South Cumbria NHS Foundation Trust. (&lt;strong&gt;2 year fixed term contract for external candidates.)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please indicate in your supporting information which inpatient area you are applying for:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Harbour Mental Health Inpatient Wards&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Guild Lodge Mental Health Inpatient Wards&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Royal Blackburn Hospital Mental Health Inpatient Wards&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ormskirk District Hospital Mental Health Inpatient Wards&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Cumbria Mental Health Inpatient Wards&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NamePractice Education Facilitator TeamEmail addresspef@lancashirecare.nhs.ukAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information and discussion regarding the role, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;pef@lancashirecare.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
